@startuml domain-scenario-model
title SafeCrowd Domain Scenario Model

left to right direction
skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam packageStyle rectangle
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam linetype ortho

package "domain" {
  package "layout contract" {
    class FacilityLayout {
      layoutId
      floors
      rooms
      doors
      connectors
      control zones
      measurement regions
    }

    class Floor {
      levelIndex
      elevation
    }

    class Room {
      roomId
      category
      occupancy anchor
    }

    class Door {
      doorId
      width
      direction mode
    }

    class Connector {
      connectorId
      kind
      endpoints
    }

    class ConnectorModifier {
      speed factor
      queue bias
      accessibility gate
    }

    class ControlZone {
      zoneId
      name
      member references
      default access mode
    }

    class StaticObstruction {
      geometry
      clearance impact
    }

    class DynamicObstacleRule {
      ruleId
      activation window
      affected area
    }

    class MeasurementRegionSpec {
      regionId
      tracked metrics
    }
  }

  package "scenario contract" {
    class ScenarioDefinition {
      scenarioId
      name
      baseline flag
    }

    class ScenarioVariation {
      variationId
      name
      override summary
    }

    class PopulationSpec {
      population profiles
      initial placements
      dynamic sources
    }

    class PopulationProfile {
      desired speed distribution
      acceleration distribution
      spacing distribution
      connector permissions
    }

    class InitialPlacement {
      room or area
      count
    }

    class DynamicSource {
      sourceId
      schedule
      ingress rate
    }

    class EnvironmentState {
      visibility
      familiarity
      guidance signal
    }

    class ControlPlan {
      events
      behavior bindings
      route choice bindings
    }

    class ExecutionConfig {
      time limit
      sample interval
      base seed
      repeat count
    }
  }
}

FacilityLayout *-- Floor
Floor *-- Room
FacilityLayout *-- Door
FacilityLayout *-- Connector
Connector *-- ConnectorModifier
FacilityLayout *-- ControlZone
ControlZone ..> Room : member rooms
ControlZone ..> Door : member doors
ControlZone ..> Connector : member connectors
FacilityLayout *-- StaticObstruction
FacilityLayout *-- DynamicObstacleRule
FacilityLayout *-- MeasurementRegionSpec

ScenarioDefinition --> FacilityLayout : uses validated layout
ScenarioDefinition --> PopulationSpec
ScenarioDefinition --> EnvironmentState
ScenarioDefinition --> ControlPlan
ScenarioDefinition --> ExecutionConfig : default run contract

ScenarioVariation --> ScenarioDefinition : derives from baseline
ScenarioVariation ..> PopulationSpec : placement/source overrides
ScenarioVariation ..> EnvironmentState : scenario delta
ScenarioVariation ..> ControlPlan : operational delta
ScenarioVariation ..> ExecutionConfig : repeat or seed override

PopulationSpec *-- PopulationProfile
PopulationSpec *-- InitialPlacement
PopulationSpec *-- DynamicSource
InitialPlacement --> Room : anchor
DynamicSource --> Room : source anchor
PopulationProfile ..> Connector : usable restriction
ControlPlan ..> ControlZone : zone-scoped control
ControlPlan ..> DynamicObstacleRule : activate / deactivate rule

note bottom of ScenarioDefinition
  Existing `ScenarioDefinition` aggregate is kept
  as the authoring boundary.
  It decomposes into the five input contracts:
  FacilityLayout / PopulationSpec / EnvironmentState
  / ControlPlan / ExecutionConfig.
end note

note bottom of ScenarioVariation
  Variation is not a full copy of the baseline.
  It stores only the delta that matters for
  comparison and repeated execution.
end note

note bottom of PopulationSpec
  PopulationSpec is the top-level population input contract.
  It owns profile definitions, initial placements,
  and source-based inflow settings together.
end note

note bottom of ControlZone
  ControlZone stays lightweight on purpose.
  It is a named room / door / connector group,
  not a separate geometry-heavy runtime model.
end note

note bottom of DynamicSource
  Initial placement and source-based inflow
  are modeled separately so Sprint 1 execution
  can start simple and later add ingress logic
  without reshaping the whole scenario contract.
end note

note bottom of DynamicObstacleRule
  The layout keeps reusable obstacle rules,
  but activation belongs to ControlPlan
  and runtime state rather than the
  persistent topology itself.
end note

@enduml
